{"relationshipsSections":[{"kind":"relationships","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/4GLib14PointerWrapperP","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypePluginProtocol"],"type":"conformsTo","title":"Conforms To"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An interface that handles the lifecycle of dynamically loaded types."}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"kind":"symbol","variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glibobject\/typeplugin"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"topicSections":[{"generated":true,"anchor":"Initializers","title":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypePlugin\/init(_:)-3cm5a","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypePlugin\/init(_:)-62sev","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypePlugin\/init(_:)-62wpb","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypePlugin\/init(_:)-8ummq","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypePlugin\/init(_:)-92sfd","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypePlugin\/init(cPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypePlugin\/init(gconstpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypePlugin\/init(gpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypePlugin\/init(opaquePointer:)","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypePlugin\/init(raw:)-3wrt5","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypePlugin\/init(raw:)-47yum","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypePlugin\/init(retaining:)","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypePlugin\/init(retainingCPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypePlugin\/init(retainingOpaquePointer:)","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypePlugin\/init(retainingRaw:)-1688d","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypePlugin\/init(retainingRaw:)-7ym33"]},{"generated":true,"title":"Instance Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypePlugin\/ptr"],"anchor":"Instance-Properties"},{"anchor":"Default-Implementations","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypePlugin\/TypePluginProtocol-Implementations"],"generated":true,"title":"Default Implementations"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"TypePlugin"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The GObject type system supports dynamic loading of types."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It goes as follows:"}]},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The type is initially introduced (usually upon loading the module"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the first time, or by your main application that knows what modules"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"introduces what types), like this:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["new_type_id = g_type_register_dynamic (parent_type_id,","                                       \"TypeName\",","                                       new_type_plugin,","                                       type_flags);"],"syntax":"c","type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"where "},{"code":"new_type_plugin","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is an implementation of the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"GTypePlugin","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" interface."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The type’s implementation is referenced, e.g. through","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[func"},{"code":"GObject.TypeClass.ref","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] or through [func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GObject.type_create_instance"},{"text":"]","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"(this is being called by [ctor"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GObject.Object.new"},{"text":"]) or through one of the above","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"done on a type derived from "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"new_type_id"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This causes the type system to load the type’s implementation by calling"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[method","type":"text"},{"code":"GObject.TypePlugin.use","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] and [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GObject.TypePlugin.complete_type_info"},{"text":"]","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"on "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"new_type_plugin"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"At some point the type’s implementation isn’t required anymore, e.g. after","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GObject.TypeClass.unref"},{"text":"] or [func","type":"text"},{"code":"GObject.type_free_instance","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"]","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(called when the reference count of an instance drops to zero).","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This causes the type system to throw away the information retrieved"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"from [method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GObject.TypePlugin.complete_type_info"},{"type":"text","text":"] and then it calls"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"code":"GObject.TypePlugin.unuse","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] on "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"new_type_plugin"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Things may repeat from the second step."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"So basically, you need to implement a "},{"code":"GTypePlugin","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" type that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"carries a use_count, once use_count goes from zero to one, you need"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to load the implementation to successfully handle the upcoming"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"code":"GObject.TypePlugin.complete_type_info","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] call. Later, maybe after"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"succeeding use\/unuse calls, once use_count drops to zero, you can","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"unload the implementation again. The type system makes sure to call","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[method","type":"text"},{"code":"GObject.TypePlugin.use","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] and [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GObject.TypePlugin.complete_type_info"},{"text":"]","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"again when the type is needed again."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"[class"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypeModule","isActive":true},{"text":"] is an implementation of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTypePlugin"},{"text":" that","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"already implements most of this except for the actual module loading and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"unloading. It even handles multiple registered types per module."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypePlugin","isActive":true},{"text":" type acts as an owner of an underlying ","type":"text"},{"code":"GTypePlugin","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"It provides the methods that can operate on this data type through "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypePluginProtocol"},{"type":"text","text":" conformance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypePlugin"},{"text":" as a strong reference or owner of a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTypePlugin"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypePluginRef","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" (instead of "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypePlugin"},{"type":"text","text":") for a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying "},{"code":"GTypePlugin","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}]}],"name":"Note","type":"aside","style":"note"}]}],"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject"]]},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypePlugin"},"metadata":{"symbolKind":"class","externalID":"s:10GLibObject10TypePluginC","modules":[{"name":"GLibObject"}],"role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Class","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"TypePlugin","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"TypePlugin"}],"title":"TypePlugin"},"references":{"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/TypePlugin/init(gpointer:)":{"role":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Optional initialiser from a non-mutating ","type":"text"},{"t